observations.recommendation:
7.5	We recommend the Management to:
Require the Municipal Planning and Development Officer to strictly adhere the provisions of DILG-DBM Joint Circular No. 2011-1 dated April 13, 2011;
Ensure that 20% Development Fund be fully utilized to achieve the optimum desirable  socio-economic and environmental development;

8.4	We recommend that Management:
Prepare LDRRMFIP for the DRRM program annually in the prescribed format required under COA Circular No. 2012-002;
Direct the concerned officer to prepare and submit the Report on Sources and Utilization of DRRMF certified correct by the Municipal Accountant in prescribed form on or before the 15th day after the end of each month, through the LDRRMC and LDC, to the COA Auditor of the municipality;

observations.managementAction:
We recommended and Management agreed to:

Require the end-user offices to submit the PPMP in September of the budget year to the BAC Secretariat which shall consolidate the same in coordination with the Municipal Budget Officer for the funding allocation, into the Municipality’s consolidated APP for the LCE’s approval and integration in the LCE’s executive budget, and observe Sections 7.3.5 and 7.4 of the IRR, and other related issuances in the APP subsequent updating/revision considering the approved appropriation;

Undertake the bulk procurement based on the    APP from the PS-DBM, and if they are not available thereat, adopt the public bidding as the general rule in the procurement of the supplies, materials and other pertinent MOOE items, and equipment procurement.
